Green Party leader steps down, provincial Green leader says he is staying put}}</ref>\n*Shawn Setyo, Leader of the [[Saskatchewan Green Party]] (2016\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ckom.com/2019/11/04/provincial-green-party-leader/|title=Provincial Green Party leader \u2018not taken by surprise\u2019 by May\u2019s departure|first=Brady|last=Lang}}</ref>\n*[[Andrew Weaver]], Leader of the [[Green Party of British Columbia]] (2015\u20132020), MLA for [[Oak Bay-Gordon Head]] (2013\u2013present)<ref>{{cite news |last1=Larsen |first1=Karin |title=Andrew Weaver says he'll step down as B.C. Green Party leader |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/andrew-weaver-1.5311543? |accessdate=21 November 2019 |publisher=[[CBC News]] |date=7 October 2019 |quote=Weaver said he has no intentions of running federally.}}</ref>\n*[[Jody Wilson-Raybould]], former [[Liberal Party of Canada|Liberal]] cabinet minister and Independent MP for [[Vancouver Granville]] (2015\u2013present)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/checkup/what-s-preventing-men-from-talking-about-their-mental-health-1.5369414/despite-speculation-wilson-raybould-says-she-has-no-plans-to-seek-green-leadership-1.5371768|title=Despite speculation, Wilson-Raybould says she has no plans to seek Green leadership|date=November  24, 2019|work=CBC News|access-date=November  24, 2019}}</ref>\n*Richard Zurawski, [[Halifax City Council]]lor for District 12, Green Party candidate for [[Halifax West]] in 2015 and 2019<ref>{{cite web|first=Meghan|last=Groff|url=https://www.halifaxtoday.ca/local-news/theres-lots-of-work-to-be-done-roberts-reacts-to-new-roll-as-interim-leader-of-green-party-1830439|title='There's lots of work to be done' : Roberts reacts to new role as interim leader of Green Party|website=Halifax Today|access-date=November 7, 2019|date=November 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Green Party of Canada leadership elections]]\n*[[2020 Conservative Party of Canada leadership election]]\n